originalText.text:
Where to begin! When my husband and I were looking for a wedding photographer, we really needed to find someone who we connected with and felt comfortable around. I am not someone who is particularly at ease posing for the camera, but I really didn't want to come across looking awkwardly rigid. It was also important that we worked with someone who had experience with queer weddings, so we didn’t feel pushed into tropes that didn’t feel right. I am So grateful that we met Kelly.

Kelly was just incredible to work with. First, she immediately put us at ease and took the time to understand what we were hoping to capture from our day. On the day of the wedding, she expertly corralled our family and friends for group photos in a way that was warm and engaging, while keeping things moving. She captured candids from the ceremony, the dinner, and the dance floor, while somehow managing to render herself invisible. I really wanted to make sure we captured all the moments we ourselves didn’t get to see and she was everywhere.

Most importantly, the photos turned stunningly. Kelly brings an absolutely infectious enthusiasm to her work and was just a blast to be around. Kelly is just the best and we are beyond thrilled with the memories she captured. Cannot recommend her highly enough!

originalText.text: We had such a blast shooting our engagement photos with Kelly at Industry City in Brooklyn! She made the process really fun - coaching us through different poses and putting us at ease during our session. We couldn't be happier with how our photos turned out. Kelly was able to capture the love and playfulness of our relationship, which we really appreciated.

originalText.text:
Kelly took my fiancée's and my engagement photos in January 2023. We were both super nervous -- we had never had professional photos taken and can be awkward in front of a camera -- but Kelly put us immediately at ease. She helped at every step of the way, even consulting on our outfits and my makeup to ensure we were dressed in a way that would translate well to photographs. She also made the process playful and fun.

Our session with Kelly was one of the first she shot with a manual camera (as opposed to the automatic digital cameras most photographers used). It was clearly a complex process for her -- and one only someone absolutely in love with photography would ever commit to! -- but the photos turned out amazingly. The colors were brighter, clearer, and more vibrant than I could have ever imagined.

I am so grateful to Kelly and happy to have found her work online. Were we not getting married in another country with a near-impossible visa process for wedding photographers, we would hire her for our wedding in an instant!! I truly could not recommend her more highly.

originalText.text: Cannot say enough good things about Kelly, who took amazing photos of our wedding and was a joy to work with. She has the kind of energy you want to be around and have around you on your big day. She easily accommodated our schedule (having ceremony/reception split across two days), did a full-on engagement shoot and info session with us ahead of time to go over everything (and gave great advice), and then captured everything perfectly -- could not be more obsessed with the final product, whether it's the more formal/posed ceremony shots or the sweaty dancefloor shots. My husband and I actually gasped in delight at some of the details she captured. Kelly has an incredible eye for this stuff and incredible vibes to match.

originalText.text: Kelly is an incredible photographer, professional, and person. She was the most organized vendor that we had the pleasure of working with (by a LOT!), which made the entire process easy and great. For our engagement shoot and the wedding itself, her photos are simply stunning! We wanted photos that were vibrant, colorful, and full of joy. She nailed it. She has wonderful energy, a kind heart, and a steady demeanor under stress. We highly, highly recommend Kelly!
